race.description: Golden State Juvenile Fillies S. Stakes
race.comment: TOO SASSY (7) is a progressive type still in first campaign but off to a great start to career. Recorded back to back wins with a 3 length success over 1106m at Listed level at this track (Dirt) last time. Won only start here and shapes as a key chance again. MISS KONA (4) was an impressive maiden winner last time out, scoring by 1.5 lengths over 1207m at this track (Dirt). Sparingly raced and has more to offer. Looks well placed and she is worth including. LIBERATION (12) reunites with J J Hernandez after scoring with ease over 1308m at Santa Anita (Dirt) last time. Should be prominent despite the awkward gate. One of the main contenders. CASHED (6) was a most impressive maiden winner over 1207m at Santa Anita (Dirt) last time out, scoring by 2.25 lengths. Is lightly raced and has plenty of scope for improvement. Harder here but should be involved in the finish.
